{"1540960":{"success":true,"data":{"type":"game","name":"Underworld Idle","steam_appid":1540960,"required_age":0,"is_free":true,"detailed_description":"Underworld Idle is an idle game about underworld management.<br><br>The basic mechanics: higher-order units create lower-order units. If you've played games like Swarm Simulator or Antimatter Dimensions, you should be familiar with these mechanics. However, in Underworld Idle I present my own take on these mechanics.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Game Features<\/h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Factions (demons, undead, utopians, and blackseekers). Each faction is responsible for producing its own resource. <br><\/li><li>Mechanics of creating units. For example, higher demons create lower demons, and so on. The same about units of undead, drowners and warlocks.<br><\/li><li>Infinite progression. Start with a small number of resources and expand into a long list of units and huge numbers.<br><\/li><li>Infernal Contracts - Prestige Mechanics.<br><\/li><li>A variety of locations: lab with energy crystals, junkyard, library with grimoire (containing dark spells).<\/li><\/ul>","about_the_game":"Underworld Idle is an idle game about underworld management.<br><br>The basic mechanics: higher-order units create lower-order units. If you've played games like Swarm Simulator or Antimatter Dimensions, you should be familiar with these mechanics. However, in Underworld Idle I present my own take on these mechanics.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Game Features<\/h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Factions (demons, undead, utopians, and blackseekers). Each faction is responsible for producing its own resource. <br><\/li><li>Mechanics of creating units. For example, higher demons create lower demons, and so on. The same about units of undead, drowners and warlocks.<br><\/li><li>Infinite progression. Start with a small number of resources and expand into a long list of units and huge numbers.<br><\/li><li>Infernal Contracts - Prestige Mechanics.<br><\/li><li>A variety